in Cambodia, and both of them are freely
available on the internet.

231
00:16:04,770 --> 00:16:07,330
So in summary, ceramic filtration is a
fast

232
00:16:07,330 --> 00:16:11,000
growing and exciting sector within
household water treatment.

233
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:13,795
Ceramic pot filters can be locally
produced, though

234
00:16:13,795 --> 00:16:17,140
it's important to have a strong quality
assurance program.

235
00:16:17,140 --> 00:16:21,470
And there are examples and resources to
help production facilities do that.

236
00:16:22,800 --> 00:16:27,730
Ceramic filtration involves a variety of
removal mechanisms, including primarily

237
00:16:27,730 --> 00:16:33,780
physical, but also electrostatic and
chemical with the use of colloidal silver.

238
00:16:33,780 --> 00:16:36,410
However, removal of pathogens is mixed.

239
00:16:36,410 --> 00:16:38,640
Protozoa tend to be well removed.

240
00:16:38,640 --> 00:16:41,410
Bacteria fairly well removed.

241
00:16:41,410 --> 00:16:44,880
And viruses, not terribly well removed at
all.

242
00:16:44,880 --> 00:16:48,890
Still, ceramic filters are very user
friendly,

243
00:16:48,890 --> 00:16:51,540
and tend to have high user satisfaction
rates.
